## 4. BACKEND CHANGES REQUIRED FOR ANDROID V1

All other backend systems are shared with iOS and require no changes.
Only these two additions are needed before Android v1 can fully ship:

### FCM Token Storage
- Supabase needs to store per-user FCM tokens alongside APNs tokens.
- Required DB change: `profiles` (or a separate `device_tokens` table) must support
  a `fcm_token TEXT NULL` column.
- All Edge Functions that send push notifications (`booking-confirmed`,
  `game-cancelled-notify`, `club-announcement-notify`, `club-chat-push`,
  `waitlist-promoted`) must be updated to send to both APNs and FCM targets.
- This is a **blocker** for Android push notifications.

### Deep Link Domain Verification
- `bookadink://` custom scheme works without domain verification.
- If App Links (HTTPS) are desired for shareable URLs, a `.well-known/assetlinks.json`
  file must be hosted at the app's domain.
- Not a hard blocker for v1 — custom scheme is sufficient.

---

## 5. BLOCKERS BEFORE IMPLEMENTATION CAN BEGIN

| Blocker | Required Action | Owner |
|---|---|---|
| FCM token storage | Add `fcm_token` column to profiles or create `device_tokens` table | Backend |
| FCM push sending | Update all 5 push-sending Edge Functions to support FCM | Backend |
| Stripe Android publishable key | Confirm `SupabaseConfig.stripePublishableKey` is accessible to Android build | Backend/iOS |
| Google Pay merchant ID | Register `bookadink` merchant with Google Pay API console | Business |
| `bookadink://` scheme | Register custom scheme intent filter (no external dependency) | Android |
| Test Supabase project | Confirm Android can connect to same Supabase project as iOS (no separate instance) | Backend |

---

## 6. EXPLICIT NON-GOALS FOR V1

- Do NOT implement any club owner or admin screen.
- Do NOT implement Google Play Billing — Stripe handles all payments (see `platform_adaptation.me §10`).
- Do NOT implement custom image upload.
- Do NOT create new Supabase tables or RPCs (beyond FCM token storage in §4).
- Do NOT implement offline mode or local DB caching beyond in-memory state.
- Do NOT implement push notification preferences or muting in v1.
- Do NOT implement a DUPR integration or chart.
